526
00:39:25,853 --> 00:39:27,844
- Want one, Max?
- Sure.

527
00:39:30,893 --> 00:39:34,249
- How'd that go?
- The usual.

528
00:39:34,293 --> 00:39:37,490
And draw one of those for my friend here.

529
00:39:37,533 --> 00:39:41,208
Yes, they were civil for about two minutes.

530
00:39:41,253 --> 00:39:45,246
And after that uncivil for a while,
then rude, then insulting.

531
00:39:45,293 --> 00:39:47,488
It stopped just short of fisticuffs.

532
00:39:48,053 --> 00:39:51,090
I don't know if I've told you, Bea, but...

533
00:39:53,893 --> 00:39:55,884
in my experience...

534
00:39:56,893 --> 00:40:01,284
most human beings
are selfish, greedy, venal, unprincipled,

535
00:40:01,333 --> 00:40:04,882
utterly irredeemable shit-eaters.

536
00:40:05,533 --> 00:40:07,922
So I have mentioned it?

537
00:40:07,973 --> 00:40:12,091
- You should have that thing removed.
- Max.

538
00:40:14,853 --> 00:40:16,332
What thing?

539
00:40:16,373 --> 00:40:21,163
I'm always afraid that it's going to explode
when I'm talking to you.

540
00:40:21,213 --> 00:40:26,082
- What would it cost you to have it cut off?
- Don't know, never looked into it.

541
00:40:26,133 --> 00:40:28,328
Oh, boy, I would've.

542
00:40:28,373 --> 00:40:33,606
If I had that thing growing out of my forehead,
I'd have had it looked into, pronto.

543
00:40:33,653 --> 00:40:38,124
I don't know, Max, I think it might be
the source of my intelligence.

544
00:40:40,053 --> 00:40:44,490
